148
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:58,933
These two offices have served this community, the residents of this community, for a combined 66 years.

149
00:10:00,795 --> 00:10:05,657
Officer Butts, William Butts, as we know him as Buttsy, we refer to him as.

150
00:10:05,677 --> 00:10:09,278
34 years, Mr. President, served this community.

151
00:10:10,038 --> 00:10:19,141
You never met a nicer, kinder gentleman, always willing to help his fellow citizens, and he will be sorely missed, Mr. President.

152
00:10:19,861 --> 00:10:29,844
And then Officer Robert Kelly, the same thing, served with distinction for a number of years, was always the first to step up in line when something was needed in the community.

153
00:10:30,545 --> 00:10:34,066
And he too will be sorely missed, Mr. President.

154
00:10:34,806 --> 00:10:36,287
I hope someday we allow

155
00:10:37,427 --> 00:10:43,514
our police officers to come back and do details like they do in other communities.

156
00:10:43,534 --> 00:10:52,603
And allow them to be part of the community, Mr. President, and bring back the experience they have for a combined 66 years in this community.

157
00:10:52,643 --> 00:10:55,927
So someday, I hope to see that come to fruition.

158
00:10:56,727 --> 00:11:14,576
And just one other point, Mr. President, I'd like to make while honoring these two officers, is just recently we all received a call, a reverse 911 call, very serious matter about a woman that was lost within our community on a very cold night, Mr. President.

159
00:11:14,896 --> 00:11:25,402
A very dangerous situation, and the way it was handled by Meffitt Police, the number of cars, the number of officers that were on foot, the number of residents that had gone out in the community.

160
00:11:25,782 --> 00:11:29,705
I know Councilor Scott Pelley is aware of some firsthand.

161
00:11:31,406 --> 00:11:40,832
Honestly, our whole department needs to be congratulated on their fine work, Mr. President, in bringing this woman back to safety.

162
00:11:41,452 --> 00:11:48,056
And I just want to personally thank, on behalf of this council, the entire police department, how they handled that situation.

163
00:11:48,236 --> 00:11:48,557
Thank you.

164
00:11:49,408 --> 00:11:50,108
Councilor Scott Beally.

165
00:11:50,548 --> 00:11:50,889
Thank you.

