295
00:21:01,074 --> 00:21:02,575
And I think more often than not,

296
00:21:03,803 --> 00:21:08,745
Those meetings become more, we're asking questions probably that are more than just budget related questions.

297
00:21:08,805 --> 00:21:10,726
Sometimes they're policy questions and whatnot.

298
00:21:11,566 --> 00:21:31,274
So this here tonight is basically a proactive approach that I'm asking President Carbiello if in the upcoming months of February, March, April, and May, if you could schedule pre-budget hearings with each of our department heads to go over their current budget,

299
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:41,203
To take a look at the goals and objectives to see if they're accomplishing

300
00:21:42,852 --> 00:21:46,654
what they've said that their goals and objectives are for this current year.

301
00:21:47,494 --> 00:21:56,299
So basically, it's a proactive approach, and it gives us an opportunity to ask department heads questions that sometimes aren't even budget related.

302
00:21:57,040 --> 00:22:01,802
So it's to hopefully streamline the budget process when we discuss the budget in June.

303
00:22:02,603 --> 00:22:08,706
So I think that we have to pass this budget, or actually pass or reject this budget each year.

304
00:22:12,278 --> 00:22:20,325
This is really large, and we need to make sure that we have all the information that we need to make that decision.

305
00:22:20,605 --> 00:22:26,130
And I think meeting with department heads more than once a year is something that we should be doing.

306
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:31,422
